track_notes: This route is intended to get you from Rte 96 in Coyote, NM to the parking spot for 9599 W5N/SE-022
This is a very modest hike. There is an unmarked gate that you can go through and then a rough trail leads directly to the summit.

Take State Hwy 126 east from Cuba. A few tenths east of the Rio de las Vacas campground turn onto FR 103 and proceed easterly. At (36.0361, -106.7013) turn east (right) onto FR 315 and continue easterly on 315 to a sharp bend at (36.02796, -106.65767) and turn north (left) onto a primitive 2 track. Take this 2 track a few tenths to a saddle east of the summit of 9599 at (36.0312, -106.6573). Park here and hike west 0.4 miles up a moderate trail to the summit. FRs 103 ad 315 are in excellent shape and can be driven by any vehicle. The 2 track at the end requires a vehicle with reasonable clearance but could be easily hiked if need be. This GPS track was made with my phone - ignore the considerable vertical noise.
